  "prompt": "How do I buy a share of the Green Bay Packers' stock?",
  "response": "The Green Bay Packers are unique in professional sports because they are a publicly-owned, non-profit organization. However, buying stock is not like buying stock in a typical company. The Packers have only offered stock sales a few times in their history, most recently in 2021. These stock offerings are rare and have some specific characteristics:\n\n1. The stock does not pay dividends\n2. It cannot be traded\n3. It does not appreciate in value\n4. It provides no financial benefits, just symbolic ownership\n\nWhen stock is available, it can be purchased directly from the team. The most recent offering in 2021 was priced at $300 per share. There's no guarantee when or if another stock offering will occur, so you would need to watch for announcements from the team.\n\nCurrently, there is no way to buy Packers stock, as no offering is active. Your best bet is to periodically check the team's official website or news sources for potential future stock sales.",
